It is also true that, after deduction of the votes of the branches, the creditors of Vitro, the creditors who sued Vitro in the United States courts, i.e. the vulture funds such as Aurelios Capital, Aurelios Convergencia, Elliot Internacional and Liverpool Limited, had not obtained a majority.
The vote would have been 45% against 37%.
This is not taken into account by the Court of Appeal.
On the other hand, there is vitriol blame for its difficult situation from 2008 onwards in the context of the great economic crisis in the United States that gave the country blows.
For this reason, the González Sada family filed a complaint before the same Court of Appeal so that the vote would take place in the plenary, i.e. of all the judges, because only three of them voted.
